thread.title_full: Ollie's Bargain Outlet to trade on Nasdaq Thursday - MarketWatch

author: By     Claudia Assis
title: Ollie's Bargain Outlet to trade on Nasdaq Thursday
text: Ollie's Bargain Outlet Holdings Inc. said Wednesday it priced its initial public offering at $16 a share, and it expects shares to begin trading on the Nasdaq Thursday under the ticker "olli". The discount retailer is offering 8.925 million shares of common sock, with proceeds to be used to repay debt. J.P. Morgan, Jefferies, and Bank of America Merrill Lynch are the offering's joint book runners.
